  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-14">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-8 text-center">Whistleblowing Law — Common Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4" id="faq-list">
        {[
          { q: 'What is a protected disclosure under UK whistleblowing law?', a: 'A protected disclosure is a report made by a worker (as defined by the Public Interest Disclosure Act 1998, which inserted sections 43A–43L into the Employment Rights Act 1996) with a reasonable belief that it is in the public interest, revealing one of six qualifying types of wrongdoing: a criminal offence, a breach of a legal obligation, a miscarriage of justice, a health and safety danger, environmental damage, or a cover-up of any of the above.' },
          { q: 'Do I need to be an employee to be protected?', a: 'No. The Public Interest Disclosure Act 1998 protects a broad category of workers, including employees, agency workers, NHS workers, contractors, and trainees. You do not need a minimum length of service.' },
          { q: 'Does my concern have to be correct to be protected?', a: 'No. You need a reasonable belief that wrongdoing is occurring, not certainty. You are protected even if you turn out to be wrong, as long as you acted honestly and reasonably.' },
          { q: 'What is the time limit for a whistleblowing detriment claim?', a: 'You must submit your claim to an employment tribunal within 3 months minus 1 day of the detriment occurring. For dismissal, it is 3 months minus 1 day from your dismissal date. You must first contact ACAS for Early Conciliation before filing.' },
          { q: 'Is there a cap on compensation for whistleblowing dismissal?', a: 'No. Unlike standard unfair dismissal, compensation for whistleblowing-related dismissal is uncapped. Tribunals can award very substantial sums in serious cases, including loss of earnings, injury to feelings, and future loss.' },
        ].map((item, i) => (
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm overflow-hidden">
            <button class="faq-toggle w-full flex items-center justify-between p-5 text-left" data-index={i}>
              <span class="font-heading font-semibold text-text-primary text-sm pr-4">{item.q}</span>
              <svg class="faq-icon flex-shrink-0 transition-transform" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-body hidden px-5 pb-5">
              <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">{item.a}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
